logr::put("## MAPS VARIABLE OPTIONS BASED ON SDTM_METADATA CODELISTS") di_map_options <- function(x) { # Collect variable names from the dataset cols <- base::colnames(x) # Collect date variable names from the dataset cols_dtc <- cols[stringr::str_detect(base::colnames(x), "DTC_|OCMST(M|D|Y)|_(DD|MM|YY)")] # Collect non-date variable names from the dataset cols_var <- cols[-which(cols %in% cols_dtc)] # For loop to map nonb-date variable options from source variables for (i in base::which(cols %in% cols_var)) { # Determine unique CODELISTNAME (grouping name) indx <- which(sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` %in% cols[i]) gname = base::unique(sdtm_dictionary$`Optiongroup name`[indx]) # If the variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # and returns character(0) sets conditions for next if(length(indx) < 1) { gname = 1 } # If the variable is in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` but # no sdtm_dictionary$`Optiongroup name` sets conditions for next if(is.na(gname)) { gname = 1 } # If variable does not exist in sdtm_code$sourcevariable move to next variable if(gname == 1) { next } else { # Filter the sdtm_code based on unique CODELISTNAME lookup <- base::data.frame(sdtm_code) %>% dplyr::filter(., CODELISTNAME %in% gname) %>% dplyr::select(., sourcevalue, CODEDVALUE) # Map map variable options from sourcevalue to CODEVALUE via lookup x[,i] <- sapply(x[,i], function(y) lookup$CODEDVALUE[match(y, lookup$sourcevalue)]) } } if(length(cols_dtc) < 1) { return(x) } else { # For loop to map variable date (DAY. MONTH) options from source variables for (ii in base::which(cols %in% cols_dtc)) { # Maps MONTH variables, DERIVES "01" if MONTH == UNK if(stringr::str_detect(cols[ii], "DTC_MM|DTC_M|OCMSTM|_MM")) { # Filter the sdtm_code based on unique CODELISTNAME lookup <- base::data.frame(sdtm_code) %>% dplyr::filter(., CODELISTNAME %in% "MONTH") %>% dplyr::select(., sourcevalue, CODEDVALUE) # Map map variable options from sourcevalue to CODEVALUE via lookup x[,ii] <- sapply(x[,ii], function(y) lookup$CODEDVALUE[match(y, lookup$sourcevalue)]) } # Maps DAY variables, DERIVES "01" if DAY == UN if(stringr::str_detect(cols[ii], "DTC_DD|DTC_D|OCMSTD|_DD")) { # Filter the sdtm_code based on unique CODELISTNAME lookup <- base::data.frame(sdtm_code) %>% dplyr::filter(., CODELISTNAME %in% "DAY") %>% dplyr::select(., sourcevalue, CODEDVALUE) # Map map variable options from sourcevalue to CODEVALUE via lookup x[,ii] <- sapply(x[,ii], function(y) lookup$CODEDVALUE[match(y, lookup$sourcevalue)]) } # Ignores any mapping of YEAR variables if(stringr::str_detect(cols[ii], "DTC_YY|DTC_Y|OCMSTY|_YY")){ # x[,ii] <- base::sapply(x[,ii], # function(y) base::ifelse(base::is.na(x[,ii]), "9999", # base::unlist(x[,ii]))) } # Collect time variable names from the dataset cols_tm <- cols[stringr::str_detect(base::colnames(x), "TM|TIM|FSWO")] } } x }

logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFSTDTC) x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }
Based in numeric value in visit STDTC inputs. I.e., V1_DD

logr::put("## DERIVE DTC, STDTC, and ENDTC from --DTC_YY, --DTC_MM, --DTC_DD") sv <- sv %>% ## Derive DTC, STDTC, and ENDTC from --DTC_YY, --DTC_MM, --DTC_DD variables ## The unite function is used to combine YEAR-MM-DD to derive --DTC variables ## The function lubridate:ymd(x) ensures the format is ISO8601 # Site visit 1 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC1', 'V1_YY', 'V1_MM', 'V1_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., SVSTDTC1 = lubridate::ymd(SVSTDTC1)) %>% # Site visit 2 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC2', 'V2_YY', 'V2_MM', 'V2_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., SVSTDTC2= lubridate::ymd(SVSTDTC2)) %>% # Site visit 3 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC3', 'V3_YY', 'V3_MM', 'V3_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., SVSTDTC3 = lubridate::ymd(SVSTDTC3)) %>% # Site visit 4 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC4', 'V4_YY', 'V4_MM', 'V4_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., SVSTDTC4 = lubridate::ymd(SVSTDTC4)) %>% # Site visit 5 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC5', 'V5_YY', 'V5_MM', 'V5_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., SVSTDTC5 = lubridate::ymd(SVSTDTC5)) %>% # Site visit 6 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC6', 'V6_YY', 'V6_MM', 'V6_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., SVSTDTC6 = lubridate::ymd(SVSTDTC6)) %>% # Site visit 7 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC7', 'V7_YY', 'V7_MM', 'V7_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., SVSTDTC7 = lubridate::ymd(SVSTDTC7))
Based in numeric value in visit STDTC inputs. I.e., V1_DD: dplyr::mutate(., VISITNUM = gsub("[^0-9.-]", "", VISITNUM))

Asssigned based on VISITNUM: dplyr::mutate(., VISIT = paste0("Visit ", VISITNUM)) logr::put("## Recode Visit 1 Screening & Baseline from Visit 1") sv_visit$VISIT[sv_visit$VISITNUM == 1] <- "Visit 1 Screening & Baseline"
All visits are pre-specified, thus value is set to "Y"

All occurance is determined by VXYN variables for each visit (i.e., V1YN): logr::put("## RESHAPE SVOCCUR FROM WIDE TO LONG AND MAP TO VISITS") sv_cols_occur <- sv_cols[str_detect(sv_cols, "YN")] sv_cols_occur <- c(sv_cols_occur, "USUBJID") sv_occur <- sv %>% dplyr::select_at(., sv_cols_occur) %>% tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = sv_cols_occur[-c(8)], values_to = "SVOCCUR") sv_visit$SVOCCUR <- sv_occur$SVOCCUR
All visit occur in a single setting, thus SVENDTC is derived from SVSTDTC; time data is not collected

Hardcode to the planned study day: logr::put("## HARDCODE/DERIVE PLANNED VISITDY AND CONTACT METHOD FROM PROTOCOL") sv_visit$VISITDY <- ifelse( sv_visit$VISITNUM == 1, 1, ifelse(sv_visit$VISITNUM == 2, 42, ifelse(sv_visit$VISITNUM == 3, 84, ifelse(sv_visit$VISITNUM == 4, 126, ifelse(sv_visit$VISITNUM == 5, 168, ifelse(sv_visit$VISITNUM == 6, 252, 364))))))
Hardcode to the study visit: sv_visit$SVCNTMOD <- ifelse(!sv_visit$VISITNUM %in% c("2","4"), "CLINIC VISIT", "TELEPHONE VISIT")
SE is created from SV: se <- as.data.frame(sv) # Hardcode to the study number: SESEQ <- VISITNUM
# Hardcode to the VISITNUM: se$ELEMENT <- ifelse(se$VISITNUM %in% c(1,2,3), "Masked Phase", ifelse(se$VISITNUM %in% c(4,5), "Open-label Phase", "Open-label Extension Phase"))
# Hardcode to the VISITNUM: se$ETCD <- ifelse(se$VISITNUM %in% c(1,2,3), "MASKED", ifelse(se$VISITNUM %in% c(4,5), "OPEN", "OPENEXT"))
Asssigned based on VISITNUM, which equals TAETORD

# Hardcode to the VISITNUM: se$EPOCH <- ifelse(se$VISITNUM %in% c(1), "Screening & Baseline", ifelse(se$VISITNUM %in% c(2,3), "Treatment 1", ifelse(se$VISITNUM %in% c(4,5), "Treatment 2", "Follow-up")))

Assigned based on VISITNUM & SVENDTC & EOP: logr::put("## MAPS SEENDTC TO THE NEXT VISIT -1 DAY OR END OF PARTICIPATION") di_seendtc <- function(x) { ## Capture end of participation date if available xx <- db %>% tidyr::unite(., col = 'SE.SEENDTC', "DS_YY", "DS_MM", "DS_DD", sep = '-', remove = FALSE) %>% dplyr::select(., USUBJID, SE.SEENDTC) ## Replace missing dates with NA xx$SE.SEENDTC[xx$SE.SEENDTC == "NA-NA-NA"] <- NA ## Define the end of participation date eop <- xx$SE.SEENDTC[xx$USUBJID %in% x$USUBJID[1]] ## Assign an index for the first missing date (NA) in SESTDTC indx <- which(is.na(x$SESTDTC))[1] ## Apply an end of participation date if applicable to the last SESTDTC x$SESTDTC[indx] <- eop ## Define the end of the SESTDTC period by the next SESTDTC - 1 day x$SEENDTC <- dplyr::lead(x$SESTDTC, n = 1, default = NA) -1 ## IF subject has no EOP date, end the function if (is.na(eop)) { xxx <- x %>% dplyr::select(STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID, SESEQ, ETCD, ELEMENT, TAETORD, EPOCH, SESTDTC, SEENDTC, SESTDY,SEENDY) xxx } else ## Define the EOP as the last element and return the dates x$SEENDTC[indx] <- eop xxx <- x %>% dplyr::select(STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID, SESEQ, ETCD, ELEMENT, TAETORD, EPOCH, SESTDTC, SEENDTC, SESTDY,SEENDY) xxx }
Assigned based on group_by and arrange ordering: ie <- ie %>% dplyr::group_by(., USUBJID) %>% dplyr::arrange(.,STUDYID, USUBJID, IETESTCD) %>% dplyr::mutate(.,IESEQ = 1:length(USUBJID))

Hardcoded to original results (IEORRES): ie_ieoc <- ie %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = ie_cols_ieoc) %>% tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = all_of(ie_cols_ieoc[-c(1:10)]), values_to = "IEORRES", names_to = "IETESTCD") %>% dplyr::mutate(., IESTRESC = ifelse(IEORRES == "1" , "Yes", ifelse(IEORRES == "0" , "No", NA)))
Hardcod to first visit: dplyr::mutate(., VISITNUM = "1")
Hardcod to first visit: dplyr::mutate(., VISIT = "Visit 1 Screening & Baseline")
Hardcod to first visit: dplyr::mutate(., VISITDY = "0")
Hardcode to ICFDTC in ymd format: ie <- db %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = ie_cols) %>% dplyr::mutate(., DOMAIN = "IE") %>% dplyr::mutate(., IEDTC = dmy(ICFDTC))

logr::put("## DERIVE STUDYDAYS VARIABLES AS REQUIRED") logr::put("## NOT DATES THAT ARE NOT VALID ARE RETURN NA") ie$IEDY <- sapply(1:length(ie$USUBJID), function(x) di_dy_trial(usubjid = ie$USUBJID[x], dtc = ie$IEDTC[x]))

Database variables are transposed to the IETESTCD variable: logr::put("## CREATE IE DATASET") ie_ie <- ie %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = ie_cols_ie) %>% dplyr::mutate(., IEDTC = as.character(IEDTC)) %>% tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = all_of(ie_cols_ie[-c(1:10)]), values_to = "IESTRESC", names_to = "IETESTCD")
logr::put("## ADD TEST NAME FROM SDTM DICTIONARY") ie$IETEST <- unlist(sapply(1:length(ie$IETESTCD), function(x) di_map_varlabel(ie$IETESTCD[x])))
logr::put("## ADD CATEGORY FROM DATASET TI") ie$IECAT <- sapply(1:length(ie$IETESTCD), function(x) di_map_tiiecat(ie$IETESTCD[x]))
logr::put("## ADD SUBCATEGORY FROM DATASET TI") ie$IESCAT <- sapply(1:length(ie$IETESTCD), function(x) di_map_tiiescat(ie$IETESTCD[x]))
logr::put("DERIVE --SEQ WITH DEFINED SDTM_METADATA$TOC_METADATA$DOMAINKEYS") dv <-dv %>% dplyr::group_by(., STUDYID, USUBJID, DVTERM, DVSTDTC) %>% dplyr::mutate(.,DVSEQ = 1:length(USUBJID))
dv <- dv %>% # EPOCH is derived using the EPOCH function: di_epoch_trial() dplyr::mutate(EPOCH = unlist(sapply(1:length(USUBJID), function(x) di_epoch_trial(usubjid = USUBJID[x], dtc = DVENDTC[x]))))

logr::put("ADD ASSIGNED/HARDCODED VARIABLES AS REQUIRED") dv <- data.frame(dv) %>% tidyr::unite(., col = 'DVSTDTC', 'DVST_YY', 'DVST_MM', 'DVST_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., DVSTDTC = lubridate::ymd(DVSTDTC))

logr::put(""ADD ASSIGNED/HARDCODED VARIABLES AS REQUIRED"") dv <- data.frame(dv) %>% tidyr::unite(., col = 'DVENDTC', 'DVEN_YY', 'DVEN_MM', 'DVEN_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., DVENDTC = lubridate::ymd(DVENDTC))

dv <- dv %>% # --STDY is derived using the custom STUDYDAYS function: di_dy_trial() dplyr::mutate(DVSTDY = unlist( sapply(1:length(USUBJID), function(x) di_dy_trial(usubjid = USUBJID[x], dtc = DVSTDTC[x]))))

dv <- dv %>% # --ENDY is derived using the custom STUDYDAYS function: di_dy_trial() dplyr::mutate(DVENDY = unlist( sapply(1:length(USUBJID), function(x) di_dy_trial(usubjid = USUBJID[x], dtc = DVENDTC[x]))))

logr::put("DERIVE --SEQ WITH DEFINED SDTM_METADATA$TOC_METADATA$DOMAINKEYS") ds <- ds %>% dplyr::group_by(., USUBJID) %>% dplyr::arrange(., USUBJID, DSSTDTC) %>% dplyr::mutate(.,DSSEQ = 1:length(USUBJID))

End of Particpation is from DSTERM in codelist; all others are hardcode to terms (for example): ds_v3mc <- ds %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = ds_cols_v3mc) %>% tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = "V3INVDTC", values_to = "DSSTDTC", names_to = "DSTERM") %>% dplyr::mutate(., DSTERM = ifelse(is.na(V3INV), "Double-masked Phase Not Completed", "Double-masked Phase Completed"))
All hardcode (for example): dplyr::mutate(., DSCAT = "Protocol Milestone")

All hardcode (for example): dplyr::mutate(., EPOCH = "Masked Phase") Alternatively, EOP is coded the following: logr::put("## SEARCH FOR EPOCH BASED ON DATES WITH di_epoch_trial FUNCTION") epoch <- c() for (i in 1:length(ds_eos$USUBJID)) { epoch[i] <- di_epoch_trial(usubjid = ds_eos$USUBJID[i], dtc = ds_eos$DSSTDTC[i]) print(i) } ds_eos$EPOCH <- epoch

logr::put("ADD ASSIGNED/HARDCODED VARIABLES AS REQUIRED") ds <- data.frame(ds) %>% dplyr::mutate_all(., as.character) %>% ## Derive DTC, STDTC, and ENDTC from --DTC_YY, --DTC_MM, --DTC_DD variables ## The unite function is used to combine YEAR-MM-DD to derive --DTC variables ## The function lubridate:ymd(x) ensures the format is ISO8601 dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) %>% # Disposition Event Date tidyr::unite(., col = 'DSDTC', 'DS_YY', 'DS_MM', 'DS_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Notification of Oncologist tidyr::unite(., col = 'ONNOTDTC', 'ONNOT_YY', 'ONNOT_MM', 'ONNOT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Notification of Ophthalmologist tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTDTC', 'OPNOT_YY', 'OPNOT_MM', 'OPNOT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 3 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTSCDTC', 'OPNOTDTC', 'V3SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 3 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTASDTC', 'OPNOTDTC', 'V3SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # End of Double-masked Phase tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVDTC', 'V3INV_Y', 'V3INV_M', 'V3INV_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Informed of Open-Label dplyr::mutate(., V3INV2DTC = V3INVDTC) %>% # Visit 3 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVSCDTC', 'V3INVDTC', 'V3SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 3 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVASDTC', 'V3INVDTC', 'V3SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5OL_Y', 'V5OL_M', 'V5OL_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 5 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5INVSCDTC', 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 5 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5INVASDTC', 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase Continuation tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6OL_Y', 'V6OL_M', 'V6OL_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 6 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6INVSCDTC', 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 6 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6INVASDTC', 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase Continuation tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7_YY', 'V7_MM', 'V7_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 6 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7INVSCDTC', 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 6 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7INVASDTC', 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) ds[apply(ds, 2, str_detect, "9999")] <- NA
Dates are united from components and used to define DSSDTC: ds %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = ds_cols_v1ifc) %>% tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = "ICFDTC", values_to = "DSSTDTC", names_to = "DSTERM")

logr::put("## CALCULATE STUDY DAYS FOR DATASET") dsstdy <- c() for (i in 1:length(ds$USUBJID)) { dsstdy[i] <- di_dy_trial(usubjid = ds$USUBJID[i], dtc = ds$DSSTDTC[i]) print(i) } logr::put("## ADD STUDY DAYS TO DS DATASET, ENSURE VALID DATES") ds <- ds %>% dplyr::mutate(., DSSTDTC = gsub("NA-NA-NA", NA, DSSTDTC), DSSTDY = dsstdy)
RFENDTC is the last date of dosing from the source dosing dataset
